---
import { Button, Card } from 'astro-pure/user'
import PageLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro'

const meta = {
  title: 'Projects',
  description: 'Detailed project portfolio and technical highlights'
}
---

<PageLayout {meta}>
  <Button title='Back' href='/' variant='back' />
  <main class='mt-6 lg:mt-10'>
    <div id='content-header' class='animate'>
      <h1 class='mb-6 mt-6 text-3xl font-medium sm:mt-10'>Projects</h1>
    </div>

    <section aria-label='Project details' class='animate prose mt-8 max-w-none text-base md:min-w-[45ch]' id='content'>
      <p>Detailed project portfolio and technical highlights.</p>

      <h2 id='deployment-of-a-full-body-motion-control-algorithm-for-humanoid-robots'>
        Deployment of a whole-body Control Algorithm for Humanoid Robots
      </h2>
      <Card subheading='Apr 10, 2026 - May 07, 2026'>
        <ul class='ms-4 list-disc text-muted-foreground'>
          <li>
            Motion retargeting: Performed secondary development based on the open-source GMR toolkit,
            completed kinematic adaptation for Walker Tienkung (1.73m, 65kg, 30-DoF), and successfully
            converted human motion capture data in npz, bvh, and fbx formats into executable pkl joint
            trajectories for the robot.
          </li>
          <li>
            Reinforcement learning training: Built a distributed parallel simulation environment with Isaac
            Lab/Gym and trained policies with PPO and AMP. Iteratively optimized reward design based on
            reward curve analysis, and validated Sim2Sim policy transfer in a high-fidelity MuJoCo
            environment.
          </li>
          <li>
            Real-robot deployment (Sim2Real): To address dynamics gaps on hardware, applied domain
            randomization and delayed-signal enhancement for improved robustness, and ultimately achieved
            zero-shot trajectory tracking and stable walking on the Walker Tienkung robot.
          </li>
          <li>
            Paper writing: Based on this project, summarized the research outcomes and prepared the paper
            ATOM: A Training Framework for Humanoid Behavior Foundation Models with Imperfect Data,
            currently submitted to NeurIPS 2026 (under review).
          </li>
        </ul>
        <div class='not-prose mb-3 grid grid-cols-1 gap-3 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3'>
          <video
            class='aspect-video w-full rounded-xl border object-cover'
            controls
            autoplay
            muted
            loop
            playsinline
            preload='metadata'
            poster='/images/social-card.png'
          >
            <source src='/videos/project_1_demo_1.mp4' type='video/mp4' />
            Your browser does not support the video tag.
          </video>
          <video
            class='aspect-video w-full rounded-xl border object-cover'
            controls
            autoplay
            muted
            loop
            playsinline
            preload='metadata'
          >
            <source src='/videos/project1_demo2.mov' type='video/quicktime' />
            Your browser does not support the video tag.
          </video>
          <video
            class='aspect-video w-full rounded-xl border object-cover'
            controls
            autoplay
            muted
            loop
            playsinline
            preload='metadata'
            poster='/images/social-card.png'
          >
            <source src='/videos/shoot.mp4' type='video/mp4' />
            Your browser does not support the video tag.
          </video>
        </div>
        <div class='not-prose mt-3'>
          <Button
            title='Project address'
            href='https://github.com/relliant/WholeBodyControl-PolicyTraining'
            target='_blank'
            variant='ahead'
          />
        </div>
      </Card>

      <h2 id='humanoid-robot-music-conductor'>Humanoid Robot Music Conductor</h2>
      <Card subheading='May 10, 2026 - May 21, 2026'>
        <ul class='ms-4 list-disc text-muted-foreground'>
          <li>
            Motion retargeting and denoising: Used GVHMR to extract human poses from symphony conducting
            videos. For temporal noise in dual-arm trajectories, applied filtering for smoothing, then
            remapped motion to humanoid joint space via inverse kinematics.
          </li>
          <li>
            Upper-body control model training: Built a parallel simulation environment in Isaac Lab and
            trained a stable upper-body control policy with reinforcement learning, enabling stable walking
            together with simple and reliable upper-limb motions.
          </li>
          <li>
            Control system deployment: Designed a fused architecture for dual-arm control and lower-body
            balance, and fed smoothed target joint angles into the low-level PD controller at 50Hz,
            achieving high-fidelity, jitter-free conducting motions on real hardware.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <div class='not-prose mb-3 grid grid-cols-1 gap-3 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3'>
          <video
            class='aspect-video w-full rounded-xl border object-cover'
            controls
            autoplay
            muted
            loop
            playsinline
            preload='metadata'
            poster='/images/social-card.png'
          >
            <source src='/videos/project2_demo3.mp4' type='video/mp4' />
            Your browser does not support the video tag.
          </video>
          <video
            class='aspect-video w-full rounded-xl border object-cover'
            controls
            autoplay
            muted
            loop
            playsinline
            preload='metadata'
            poster='/images/social-card.png'
          >
            <source src='/videos/project2_demo2.mov' type='video/quicktime' />
            Your browser does not support the video tag.
          </video>
          <video
            class='aspect-video w-full rounded-xl border object-cover'
            controls
            autoplay
            muted
            loop
            playsinline
            preload='metadata'
            poster='/images/social-card.png'
          >
            <source src='/videos/conducting_demo_1.mov' type='video/quicktime' />
            Your browser does not support the video tag.
          </video>
        </div>
        <div class='not-prose mt-3'>
          <Button
            title='Project address'
            href='https://github.com/relliant/WBC-data-processing'
            target='_blank'
            variant='ahead'
          />
        </div>
      </Card>

      <h2 id='simulation-and-control-of-the-tiago-mobile-manipulator-in-gazebo'>
        Simulation and Control of the TIAGo Mobile Manipulator in Gazebo
      </h2>
      <Card subheading='May 16, 2025 - May 29, 2025'>
        <ul class='ms-4 list-disc text-muted-foreground'>
          <li>
            Mobile manipulation planning: Implemented a full pick-and-place pipeline for the TIAGo mobile
            manipulator in Gazebo using ROS and MoveIt!.
          </li>
          <li>
            Motion planning and arm control: Configured the OMPL planner library (RRT and RRT*) for
            joint-space path planning and designed a custom time-parameterization method to smooth
            trajectory velocity.
          </li>
          <li>
            Autonomous navigation and obstacle avoidance: Built a navigation stack with Gmapping and Move
            Base, and combined it with ArUco pose feedback to achieve precise end-effector alignment and
            placement.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </Card>
    </section>
  </main>
</PageLayout>
